by /DC=ch/DC=cern/OU=Organic Units/OU=Users/CN=egough/CN=734735/CN=Erik Gough</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='19571#1393545668'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-02-28T00:01:08+00:00">Feb 28, 2014 12:01 AM UTC</time> by <b>Matyas Selmeci</b><a class="anchor" name="1393545668">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hi Erik,
Sorry this took so long. As Tim said, we got preempted.

I haven&#39;t been able to reproduce your exact symptoms (for me, small files were broken too), but I did get some of the segfaults you described and I think that the missing libjsig.so is causing your problem. That file is typically provided by your JRE -- on my SL6 test machine, that&#39;s java-1.7.0-openjdk. It&#39;s not in a path that the loader would find it by default though, which is why you&#39;re getting that message.

There should be a file at /usr/lib/jvm/java/jre/lib/amd64/libjsig.so. Try making a symlink to that in /usr/lib64 and restarting globus-gridftp-server. That solved it for me, anyway.

-Mat</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='19571#1393274628'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-02-24T20:43:48+00:00">Feb 24, 2014 08:43 PM UTC</time><a class="anchor" name="1393274628">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Thanks for the update Tim.  If you can think of anything else I can provide before you take a look just let me know.

by /DC=ch/DC=cern/OU=Organic Units/OU=Users/CN=egough/CN=734735/CN=Erik Gough</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='19571#1393271867'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-02-24T19:57:47+00:00">Feb 24, 2014 07:57 PM UTC</time> by <b>Tim Cartwright</b><a class="anchor" name="1393271867">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Erik&#58;

