by /DC=ch/DC=cern/OU=Organic Units/OU=Users/CN=egough/CN=734735/CN=Erik Gough</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='19571#1392741495'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-02-18T16:38:15+00:00">Feb 18, 2014 04:38 PM UTC</time> by <b>goughes@....</b><a class="anchor" name="1392741495">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hello,

I keep running into an issue when installing gridftp-hdfs on RHEL6.  I
am able to copy small files fine, but when I copy a larger file the
transfer process seg faults.  This is a standalone gridftp server that
is not a datanode in HDFS.

When I copy an 18MB input file there is no issue.

When I copy a 127MB file I get this error after the file is written and
the cksums are calculated&#58;

error&#58; an end-of-file was reached
globus_xio_system_select.c&#58;globus_l_xio_system_try_read&#58;1140&#58;
An end of file occurred

When I copy a 129MB file I get this error&#58;
error&#58; globus_xio_system_select.c&#58;globus_l_xio_system_try_write&#58;1424&#58;
System error in write&#58; Connection reset by peer
globus_xio&#58; A system call failed&#58; Connection reset by peer

All other large files have the same error.

I have attached 127.out and 128.out.  These files are the console debug
output of gridftp-hdfs-standalone.

I also attached the output of &#39;yum list installed&#39;.

I have tried different java 6 rpms with no luck&#58; sun/openjdk

Let me know if you have any thoughts.

Thanks,
-Erik

