Hi Tim,

I am currently getting this weird issue when I install the current
release version of gridftp on any RHEL6 node.  I am able to copy files
into the server up to 128MB.  Once I copy a file &#62; 128MB, the transfer
fails.  This seems like an issue where if the gridftp server has to
create more than one block in HDFS it fails with the process killed by
signal 11.

I was thinking it was an issue with our local repos, but I got the same
error when using the EPEL and OSG 3.2 repos.  I have reached out to some
other sites to get versioning information for the packages installed on
their RHEL6 nodes to see if there is an inconsistency.

Does this gridftp-hdfs package support Hadoop 2.0?

<a href='http&#58;//repo.grid.iu.edu/osg/3.2/el6/release/x86_64/gridftp-hdfs-0.5.4-9.osg.el6.x86_64.rpm' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>http&#58;//repo.grid.iu.edu/osg/3.2/el6/release/x86_64/gridftp-hdfs-0.5.4-9.osg.el6.x86_64.rpm</a>

I see that version running on our RHEL5 nodes and they seem to work
fine.

Sorry this is taking so long... one would think that installing and
testing a gridftp server would be quite trivial.

-Erik</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='19571#1392226778'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2014-02-12T17:39:38+00:00">Feb 12, 2014 05:39 PM UTC</time> by <b>Tim Theisen</b><a class="anchor" name="1392226778">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Erik Gough is having trouble getting the latest version of gridftp-hdfs working in OSG 3.2.  I will be attaching our email conversation to date.</pre></div><legend>Similar Recent Tickets <small>modified within the last 30 days</small></legend><div id="similar_tickets"><p class="muted">No similar tickets found.</p></div>
